rComments: He is a good lecturer, I find the lecture really helpful. But he doesn't care! Regardless of how good he is, if I don't get any of my grades back, that is useless, because how am I supposed to know if I learned the correct thing or not? All my other courses' final grades are out, for his course, I didn't even get my first assignment back.
He doesn't even pretend to care.

How does he manage to do everything late where we don't even get half our assignments back for the final exam, and manage to screw everyone over in the final. Maybe it's different in later years, but I went to him during office hours and he either didn't know what he was talking about or didn't care enough to answer my questions.

Overall, meh. Instructed the counting/probability portion. He is a nice/funny guy, uses simple examples in his lectures to teach. His assessments are also pretty simple for the most part. Final exam ended up being 5% of what he taught us, I dropped 12% from it. Tip: Get close to 100% in the non-exam parts (50%) and stay above average on the tests.

Will give Assignments and Midterms that are similar to past years. However, he makes the final insanely difficult. Write down every word he says. If you have questions, meet him in person always. Nice guy. Knows his stuff. Bad teacher.

I've taken 3 courses with Pancer and I'm getting tired of it. He teaches like you already have a degree in computer science and he seems to have favourite subjects he likes to spend all lecture talking about but he'll gloss over the other important concepts  - then test you on it. In short - smart guy, bad prof.
An absolute legend. Maybe the best prof at utsc. Lectures were never boring with this guy.

Does not cover the material, does not reply to emails, does not provide corrections, doesn't even give you your assignment grades. His assignment questions are so far removed from what he does teach that they are impossible without independent learning.

The course does not follow what is shown in course Syllabus. Pancer continuously broke promises in the course. The course prereq. should really be CSCA48. I wouldn't recommend taking the course before taking CSCA48. In general I wouldn't recommend you take the course at all.

Lectures were very unclear and instead of explaining concepts he would instead explain problems, making the concepts hard to understand. After doing research on the internet I found that there were rules and subjects he failed to teach or even mention.

Did not provide us enough questions to prepare us for the midterm and assignments haven't been marked yet since two months ago. Finally told us the appropriate textbook to use the week before final exam.

The midterm is quite hard, the average is around 40s. Then he bell curved the midterm. YAY And it gets better, the final exam is extremely easy compared to midterm. When I saw the final exam questions I realized I actually don't even need to study for the final,lol. Lecture is ok. No text book. Funny and cool prof, will take his class again.
